::java_proficiency_01::Which statement best defines java proficiency in Java? {
=Java proficiency means reliably designing, implementing, testing, and debugging Java programs.
~Object creation in Java is the process of allocating and initializing class instances.
~A reference chain is a sequence of object references used to reach nested data.
~Object modification changes the internal state of a mutable Java object.
}

::java_proficiency_02::Which Java construct is most directly tied to java proficiency? {
=Core language features, OOP, collections, exceptions, and tooling are essential proficiency areas.
~The == operator checks identity for object references.
~Java resolves overloaded methods at compile time using argument types.
~In Java, object variables hold references; primitives hold values directly.
}

::java_proficiency_03::Which example best demonstrates java proficiency in Java code? {
~println(int) and println(String) are classic overloading examples.
~String equality with equals() demonstrates value-style comparison.
=A proficient developer can read stack traces and locate root causes efficiently.
~Passing an object reference to a method still allows mutation of the same object.
}

::java_proficiency_04::Which is a common mistake when working with java proficiency? {
=A common mistake is memorizing syntax without understanding object semantics.
~A common mistake is using == instead of equals() for value comparison.
~A common mistake is exposing mutable internal fields directly.
~A common mistake is defining methods that do too many unrelated tasks.
}

::java_proficiency_05::Which test most directly validates java proficiency behavior? {
~A good test checks state transitions after each critical step.
=A strong proficiency test includes coding tasks plus reasoning about tradeoffs.
~Tests should cover each overloaded signature explicitly.
~A good test includes missing-link cases in deep object graphs.
}

::java_proficiency_06::Which performance/maintainability statement about java proficiency is most accurate? {
~Well-designed compound data improves readability more than using parallel primitive arrays.
=Proficiency grows by deliberate practice on real code, not only quizzes.
~Explicit sequencing improves predictability in imperative code.
~Identity matters for caching, synchronization, and aliasing behavior.
}

::java_proficiency_07::Which refactoring most improves code related to java proficiency? {
~Refactoring with intermediate variables or null-safe design improves chain readability.
~Refactoring complex sequences into named methods improves traceability.
=Refactoring and code review habits are key markers of improving proficiency.
~Refactoring shared setup into one canonical constructor reduces bugs.
}

::java_proficiency_08::Which Java API/keyword detail is most relevant to java proficiency? {
~Copy constructors or clone alternatives are used when independent copies are needed.
~final on a reference prevents rebinding, not mutation of the referenced object.
~Encapsulation helps control where and how modifications are allowed.
=Using JUnit and a debugger effectively is a practical proficiency signal.
}

::java_proficiency_09::Which debugging approach is most useful for java proficiency problems? {
~Mutation bugs are debugged by tracing who writes to the object state.
~Breakpoints on call sites and callee methods are effective for tracing behavior.
~Memory/allocation issues are debugged with profilers and GC logs.
=Profilers and logs help proficient developers diagnose performance and behavior issues.
}

::java_proficiency_10::Which statement about java proficiency is true? {
=Java proficiency includes writing readable code that others can maintain.
~Clear semantics are essential for correct APIs and collection behavior.
~Clear mutation boundaries make code easier to reason about.
~Good method definitions express one responsibility clearly.
}
